4–Deceased","1266–Female":"1266–Deceased","1264":"1264","1284":"1284","1295":"1295","1292":"1292","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1313":"1313","1311":"1311","1321":"1321","1266":"1266","1287":"1287","1276":"1276","1319":"1319","1317":"1317","Walford, Shropshire, England":"Walford, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Walford","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","habitational name from one or more of several places so named, such as Walford (Herefordshire), Walford in Leintwardine (also Herefordshire), Walford in Baschurch (Shropshire), and possibly Walford Hall in Hampton in Arden (Warwickshire), though this last may be a manorial placename deriving from the surname. The Herefordshire placenames probably derive from Old English <i>walh</i> ‘foreigner, Welshman’ (genitive plural <i>wala</i>) + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’. The Shropshire placename derives from Old English <i>wella</i> ‘well, spring, stream’ + <i>ford</i>. If it does not derive from the surname, the Warwickshire placename probably has the same etymology as the Herefordshire placenames.","perhaps occasionally a habitational name from Walford in Wimborne Minster (Dorset). The placename probably derives from Old English <i>walt</i> ‘unsteady’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Walter De Walford was born in 1290, in Walford, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Ralph De Walford, was 26 and his mother, Mrs Ralph De Walford, was 24. He married Mrs Walter De Walford in 1311, in Walford, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 5 sons."},"et":{"1290–":"1290–Surnud","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1292–1327":"1292–1327","1295–Male":"1295–Surnud","1291–Female":"1291–Surnud","1313–Male":"1313–Surnud","1315–1327":"1315–1327","1317–1327":"1317–1327","1319–Male":"1319–Surnud","1321–1319":"1321–1319","1276–Male":"1276–Surnud","1284–1319":"1284–1319","1264–Male":"1264–Surnud","1266–Female":"1266–Surnud","1264":"1264","1284":"1284","1295":"1295","1292":"1292","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1313":"1313","1311":"1311","1321":"1321","1266":"1266","1287":"1287","1276":"1276","1319":"1319","1317":"1317","Walford, Shropshire, England":"Walford, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1290–":"1290–Kuollut","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1292–1327":"1292–1327","1295–Male":"1295–Kuollut","1291–Female":"1291–Kuollut","1313–Male":"1313–Kuollut","1315–1327":"1315–1327","1317–1327":"1317–1327","1319–Male":"1319–Kuollut","1321–1319":"1321–1319","1276–Male":"1276–Kuollut","1284–1319":"1284–1319","1264–Male":"1264–Kuollut","1266–Female":"1266–Kuollut","1264":"1264","1284":"1284","1295":"1295","1292":"1292","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1315":"1315","1313":"1313","1311":"1311","1321":"1321","1266":"1266","1287":"1287","1276":"1276","1319":"1319","1317":"1317","Walford, Shropshire, England":"Walford, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1290–":"1290–Décédé","1290–Male":"1290–Décédé","1292–1327":"1292–1327","1295–Male":"1295–Décédé","